---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<BaseLayout title="Module 3: Security Assurance — CS8833 Reference" currentPath="/m3-assurance">

<div class="module-header">
  <div class="module-num">Module 03</div>
  <h2>Security Assurance</h2>
</div>

<p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Module 3 covers the second-line security assurance functions: risk register management, compliance and policy frameworks, GRC reporting and metrics, application security, and red teaming.</p>

<div class="overview-grid">
  <a href={`${base}/m3-assurance/t1-risk-register`} class="overview-card">
    <div class="card-code">Topic 1</div>
    <div class="card-title">Risk Register</div>
    <div class="card-desc">Enterprise risk register structure, risk scoring methodologies, SLAs, urgency scoring, sources and workflow, risk register fields, reporting, and RAMP exercises.</div>
  </a>
  <a href={`${base}/m3-assurance/t2-compliance-policy`} class="overview-card">
    <div class="card-code">Topic 2</div>
    <div class="card-title">Compliance &amp; Policy</div>
    <div class="card-desc">Compliance frameworks, the chain of TPRM, questionnaires, policy guiding principles, policy components, and an acceptable use policy deep dive.</div>
  </a>
  <a href={`${base}/m3-assurance/t3-reporting-metrics`} class="overview-card">
    <div class="card-code">Topic 3</div>
    <div class="card-title">Reporting &amp; Metrics</div>
    <div class="card-desc">Defining metrics, non-cyber metric examples, qualitative metrics and litmus tests, and cyber-specific metric examples for governance reporting.</div>
  </a>
  <a href={`${base}/m3-assurance/t4-appsec`} class="overview-card">
    <div class="card-code">Topic 4</div>
    <div class="card-title">Application Security</div>
    <div class="card-desc">Defining AppSec, the SESP, top vulnerability classes, threat modeling, SAST, DAST, SCA, external tools (bug bounties, ASM), and bonus concepts.</div>
  </a>
  <a href={`${base}/m3-assurance/t5-red-teaming`} class="overview-card">
    <div class="card-code">Topic 5</div>
    <div class="card-title">Red Teaming</div>
    <div class="card-desc">Red team etymology, pen testing vs. red teaming, trends, assumed breach methodology, IFF protocols, purple teaming, and reporting results.</div>
  </a>
</div>

</BaseLayout>
